Vice President Mike Pence has appointed Ambassador Debbie Birx as the White House Coronavirus Response Coordinator. Ambassador Birx, a renowned global health official and physician, will report to Vice President Pence and join the Task Force led by Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar. While continuing her work combatting HIV/AIDS globally, she will bring her expertise and coordination skills to the Coronavirus response. With three decades of experience in public health, including vaccine research and interagency coordination, Ambassador Birx has been instrumental in changing the course of the HIV pandemic. She will utilize her infectious disease, immunologic, vaccine research, and interagency coordinating capacity in her new role.